    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just hard to believe in \"hope\" or \"rekindling\" when the core is just... empty. it's like being a house that's been completely gutted by a fire. the structure is still standing, but there's nothing left inside to keep warm. it just feels like a burden to keep pretending the person inside is still there when it's really just an echo. it's exhausting to carry around a life that doesn't belong to you anymore.",
